						               													<description>The Romulan Ship Recognition Manual expands on the ships types seen in the base game Star Trek: Starship Tactical Combat Simulator, adding new variants for almost every Romulan ship in that product, as well as adding a number of new craft.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;As with the base Star Trek: Starship Tactical Combat Simulator itself, this is ostensibly an &amp;quot;expansion&amp;quot; for the Role Playing game, in that it provides more data than just the combat element requires.  3-dimension views are provided for all craft, along with extensive historical notes and background.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The book was released with two covers, each with the same internal info. In both cases, the cover of this 48-page product features a cutaway of the Romulan 'Whitewind' cruiser. However, the first release version has only the words &amp;quot;ROMULAN SHIP RECOGNITION MANUAL&amp;quot; in red block letters on the cover, while the second version has the &amp;quot;framed&amp;quot; design shared with the 2nd Edition Federation &amp;amp; Klingon SRMs.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Indicating the clear tie to the wargame, the last page presents a sheet of counters that you can photocopy and mount on cardboard for use with the tactical game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Expands:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    Star Trek: Starship Tactical Combat Simulator&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
